<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Rosh_Hashanah#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A popular <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mnemonic" title="Mnemonic">mnemonic</a> is "<i>lo adu rosh</i>" ("Rosh [Hashanah] is not on <i>adu</i>"), where <i>adu</i> has the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gematria" title="Gematria">numerical value</a> 1-4-6 (corresponding to the numbering of days in the Jewish week, in which Saturday night and Sunday daytime make up the first day).</span>
</li>
