</div></td></tr><tr><td class="navbox-abovebelow" colspan="2" style="font-size:90%;"><div>Legend: 
<p>(federal) = federal holidays, (abbreviation) = state/territorial holidays, (religious) = religious holidays, (cultural) = holiday related to a specific <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Race_and_ethnicity_in_the_United_States_Census" title="Race and ethnicity in the United States Census">racial/ethnic group</a> or <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sexual_minority" title="Sexual minority">sexual minority</a>, (week) = week-long holidays, (month) = month-long holidays, (36) = <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Title_36_of_the_United_States_Code" title="Title 36 of the United States Code">Title 36 Observances and Ceremonies</a><br />
<b>Bold</b> indicates major holidays commonly celebrated in the United States, which often represent the major celebrations of the month.<br />
</p>
See also: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lists_of_holidays" title="Lists of holidays">Lists of holidays</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hallmark_holiday" title="Hallmark holiday">Hallmark holidays</a>, public holidays in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_holidays_in_the_United_States" title="Public holidays in the United States">United States</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_holidays_in_New_Jersey" title="State holidays in New Jersey">New Jersey</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_York_State_government_holidays" title="New York State government holidays">New York</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_holidays_in_Puerto_Rico" title="Public holidays in Puerto Rico">Puerto Rico</a> and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Public_holidays_in_the_United_States_Virgin_Islands" title="Public holidays in the United States Virgin Islands">United States Virgin Islands</a>.</div></td></tr></tbody></table></div>
